
// This Hyperlambda code snippet modifies the value of the [.content] node by replacing all occurrences of the substring "](" with " (" within its current value. The [set-value] slot updates the node's value, while the [strings.replace] slot performs the string replacement operation. The first argument in [strings.replace] specifies the target substring to find, and the second argument specifies the replacement substring.
set-value:x:@.content
   strings.replace:x:@.content
      .:](
      .:" ("
